					"text" : "The timbre Map is a 2D projection of the real 6-D timbre latent space. Each cluster roughly represents each style/locutor of the dataset.\n\nThe mapping goes 2-ways between the map and the latents. 2D latents are useful for coarse control, while 6D latents correspond to finer/smoother timbre evolutions."
